      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This 1994 Mazda RX-7 (FD) is a masterclass in lightweight, front-midship engineering. It features a numbers-matching 13B-REW rotary engine with a flawlessly operational sequential twin-turbocharger system, ensuring a linear power band and immediate boost response. The chassis remains structurally perfect, retaining its factory-spec double-wishbone suspension and aluminum components for telepathic handling. Maintenance is exhaustive, including a full Viton vacuum line overhaul and recent compression benchmarks that confirm optimal apex seal integrity. Power is transferred through a precise five-speed manual gearbox to a Torsen limited-slip differential. With zero oxidation and a concours-level engine bay, this FD represents a rare opportunity to own a preserved icon of the golden era of JDM performance.",
